body: What's the opset version in your model?

Could you run this python script again your model?

```python
import onnx
import sys

from onnx import ModelProto
from google.protobuf import text_format

proto = ModelProto()

f = open(sys.argv[1], "rb")
proto.ParseFromString(f.read())
f.close()
print(proto.opset_import)
```

It will print out the opset.

It is version 9
Generated with PyTorch 1.0
Then, what's the input type of this node? I guess it's not float.

Correct. It is a tensor of bytes. One of the operations (in the network) is to cast to float. For optimization this is better because I won't have to cast and then marshal a bigger data from managed to un-managed code.

The data comes from C# bitmap (byte array with shape HWC) I would like to do the Transpose/Permute in ONNX to become CHW (and then later I convert to float before it is passed to convolutional)

>  tensor of bytes
Tensor of what?

In the spec, this op supports:

 tensor(uint8), tensor(uint16), tensor(uint32), tensor(uint64), tensor(int8), tensor(int16), tensor(int32), tensor(int64), tensor(float16), tensor(float), tensor(double), tensor(string), tensor(bool), tensor(complex64), tensor(complex128)

But in our code, we didn't implement all of them. 

Please let me know more specifically, which one do you need? Is it  tensor(uint8) or tensor(int8)?

Thanks.
I think our Transpose should support all of them except complex types.
Hi @yuslepukhin , but your change is in master branch,  not 0.3.0 release.
